  Appendix 3  9 
(viii)  determining the main gaps in knowledge about how and to what extent different 
regulatory frameworks work by conducting case studies in ADB’s developing 
member countries (DMCs); 

(ix)  preparing criteria for participating DMCs and a shortlist for DMC case studies; 

(x)  preparing a report presenting findings on the state of knowledge about how 
regulatory frameworks work in practice, the identified gaps, proposed choice of 
countries and subjects for case studies, and outline terms of reference for the 
case studies; 

(xi)  designing,  coordinating  and  supervising  the  preparation  of  case  studies, 
including the management and coordination of work by national consultants, 
work planning and scheduling, and quality control;  

(xii)  overseeing the final selection of case studies in each country; 

(xiii)  coordinating  the  development  of  case  study  methodologies  and  research 
instruments to ensure consistency, and planning and participating in workshops 
for this purpose; 

(xiv)  developing a participatory survey instrument to be used in country case studies 
to  obtain  the  opinions  of  key  government  officials  and  policy  makers, 
stakeholders, and consumers on the effectiveness of regulation of water and 
energy infrastructure and utility services;  

(xv)  overseeing and coordinating one workshop to solicit views from stakeholders 
and another to discuss the findings of the case studies for each participating 
DMC; 

(xvi)  preparing  a  report  including  (a)  country  reports  prepared  for  the  regional 
conference  and  submitted  by  the  national  consultants,  (b)  proceedings  and 
discussions of the regional workshop, and (c) recommendations for ADB; 

(xvii)  overseeing and coordinating regional  and national workshops to discuss the 
draft  final  report,  share  practical  information  on  the  challenges  faced  in 
establishing effective regulation, and identify key areas for improvement of water 
and energy regulatory reforms;  

(xviii)  organizing workshops for ADB staff on the outcomes and findings of the RETA 
with one workshop specifically for staff of the Office of the General Counsel 
(OGC); 

(xix)  supervising and coordinating tasks performed by national consultants; 

(xx)  reviewing and editing written reports of participatory surveys in each country; 
and 

(xxi)  providing inputs for an ADB publication on enhancing effective regulation of 
water  and  energy  infrastructure  services  and  preparing  other  papers  and 
submissions as required.
